Four men have been caught on CCTV robbing a service station in Tecomba, Melbourne . 
  They are wanted for five similar break-ins in the area . 
  The men filled a doona cover with $38,000 worth of cigarettes . 
  They struggled to fit the loot in the boot and dragged it alongside the car . 
  Victoria Police say they lost a third of their loot during the getaway . 
  The group broke into the service station on April 2 . 
 